block content 
    h1.bd-title#content  Reboot
    p.bd-lead Reboot, a collection of element-specific CSS changes in a single file, kickstart Bootstrap to provide an elegant, consistent, and simple baseline to build upon.
    h2#approach Approach
    p
        | Reboot builds upon Normalize, providing many HTML elements with somewhat opinionated styles using only element selectors. Additional styling is done only with classes. For example, we reboot some 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;table&gt;
        |  styles for a simpler baseline and later provide 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table
        | , 
        code.highlighter-rouge .table-bordered
        | , and more.
    p Here are our guidelines and reasons for choosing what to override in Reboot:
    ul
        li
            | Update some browser default values to use 
            code.highlighter-rouge rem
            | s instead of 
            code.highlighter-rouge em
            | s for scalable component spacing.
        li
            | Avoid 
            code.highlighter-rouge margin-top
            | . Vertical margins can collapse, yielding unexpected results. More importantly though, a single direction of 
            code.highlighter-rouge margin
            |  is a simpler mental model.
        li
            | For easier scaling across device sizes, block elements should use 
            code.highlighter-rouge rem
            | s for 
            code.highlighter-rouge margin
            | s.
        li
            | Keep declarations of 
            code.highlighter-rouge font
            | -related properties to a minimum, using 
            code.highlighter-rouge inherit
            |  whenever possible.
    h2#page-defaults Page defaults
    p
        | The 
        code.highlighter-rouge
            span.nt <html>
        |  and 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;body&gt;
        |  elements are updated to provide better page-wide defaults. More specifically:
    ul
        li
            | The 
            code.highlighter-rouge box-sizing
            |  is globally set on every element—including 
            code.highlighter-rouge *::before
            |  and 
            code.highlighter-rouge *::after
            | , to 
            code.highlighter-rouge border-box
            | . This ensures that the declared width of element is never exceeded due to padding or border.
            ul
                li
                    | No base 
                    code.highlighter-rouge font-size
                    |  is declared on the 
                    code.highlighter-rouge
                        span.nt &lt;html&gt;
                    | , but 
                    code.highlighter-rouge 16px
                    |  is assumed (the browser default). 
                    code.highlighter-rouge font-size: 1rem
                    |  is applied on the 
                    code.highlighter-rouge &lt;body&gt;
                    |  for easy responsive type-scaling via media queries while respecting user preferences and ensuring a more accessible approach.
        li
            | The 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;body&gt;
            |  also sets a global 
            code.highlighter-rouge font-family
            | , 
            code.highlighter-rouge line-height
            | , and 
            code.highlighter-rouge text-align
            | . This is inherited later by some form elements to prevent font inconsistencies.
        li
            | For safety, the 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;body&gt;
            |  has a declared 
            code.highlighter-rouge background-color
            | , defaulting to 
            code.highlighter-rouge #fff
            | .
    h2#native-font-stack Native font stack
    p
        | The default web fonts (Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, and Arial) have been dropped in Bootstrap 4 and replaced with a “native font stack” for optimum text rendering on every device and OS. Read more about 
        a(href='https://www.smashingmagazine.com/2015/11/using-system-ui-fonts-practical-guide/')
            | native font stacks in this 
            em Smashing Magazine
            |  article
        | .
    figure.highlight
        pre.
    p
        | This 
        code.highlighter-rouge font-family
        |  is applied to the 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;body&gt;
        |  and automatically inherited globally throughout Bootstrap. To switch the global 
        code.highlighter-rouge font-family
        | , update 
        code.highlighter-rouge $font-family-base
        |  and recompile Bootstrap.
    h2#headings-and-paragraphs Headings and paragraphs
    p
        | All heading elements—e.g., 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;h1&gt;
        | —and 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;p&gt;
        |  are reset to have their 
        code.highlighter-rouge margin-top
        |  removed. Headings have 
        code.highlighter-rouge margin-bottom: .5rem
        |  added and paragraphs 
        code.highlighter-rouge margin-bottom: 1rem
        |  for easy spacing.
    table
        thead
            tr
                th Heading
                th Example
        tbody
            tr
                td
                    p
                        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;h1&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
                td
