    h2#forms Forms
    p
        | Various form elements have been rebooted for simpler base styles. Here are some of the most notable changes:
    ul
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;fieldset&gt;
            | s have no borders, padding, or margin so they can be easily used as wrappers for individual inputs or groups of inputs.
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;legend&gt;
            | s, like fieldsets, have also been restyled to be displayed as a heading of sorts.
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;label&gt;
            | s are set to 
            code.highlighter-rouge display: inline-block
            |  to allow 
            code.highlighter-rouge margin
            |  to be applied.
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;input&gt;
            | s, 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;select&gt;
            | s, 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;textarea&gt;
            | s, and 
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;button&gt;
            | s are mostly addressed by Normalize, but Reboot removes their 
            code.highlighter-rouge margin
            |  and sets 
            code.highlighter-rouge line-height: inherit
            | , too.
        li
            code.highlighter-rouge &lt;textarea&gt;
            | s are modified to only be resizable vertically as horizontal resizing often “breaks” page layout.
    p These changes, and more, are demonstrated below.
    form.bd-example
        fieldset
            legend Example legend
            p
                label(for='input') Example input
                input#input(type='text', placeholder='Example input')
            p
                label(for='select') Example select
                select#select
                    option(value='') Choose...
                    optgroup(label='Option group 1')
                        option(value='') Option 1
                        option(value='') Option 2
                        option(value='') Option 3
                    optgroup(label='Option group 2')
                        option(value='') Option 4
                        option(value='') Option 5
                        option(value='') Option 6
            p
                label
                    input(type='checkbox', value='')
                    |         Check this checkbox
            p
