                    |         Option one is this and that
                label
                    input#optionsRadios2(type='radio', name='optionsRadios', value='option2')
                    |         Option two is something else that's also super long to demonstrate the wrapping of these fancy form controls.
                label
                    input#optionsRadios3(type='radio', name='optionsRadios', value='option3', disabled='')
                    |         Option three is disabled
            p
                label(for='textarea') Example textarea
                textarea#textarea(rows='3')
            p
                label(for='date') Example date
                input#date(type='date')
            p
                label(for='time') Example time
                input#time(type='time')
            p
                label(for='output') Example output
                output#output(name='result') 100
            p
                button(type='submit') Button submit
                input(type='submit', value='Input submit button')
                input(type='button', value='Input button')
            p
                button(type='submit', disabled='') Button submit
                input(type='submit', value='Input submit button', disabled='')
                input(type='button', value='Input button', disabled='')
    h2#misc-elements Misc elements
    h3#address Address
    p
        | The 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;address&gt;
        |  element is updated to reset the browser default 
        code.highlighter-rouge font-style
        |  from 
        code.highlighter-rouge italic
        |  to 
        code.highlighter-rouge normal
        | . 
        code.highlighter-rouge line-height
        |  is also now inherited, and 
        code.highlighter-rouge margin-bottom: 1rem
        |  has been added. 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;address&gt;
        | s are for presenting contact information for the nearest ancestor (or an entire body of work). Preserve formatting by ending lines with 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;br&gt;
        | .
    .bd-example
        address
            strong Twitter, Inc.
            br
            |     1355 Market St, Suite 900
            br
            |     San Francisco, CA 94103
            br
            abbr(title='Phone') P:
            |  (123) 456-7890
        address
            strong Full Name
            br
            a(href='mailto:#') first.last@example.com
    h3#blockquote Blockquote
    p
        | The default 
        code.highlighter-rouge margin
        |  on blockquotes is 
        code.highlighter-rouge 1em 40px
        | , so we reset that to 
        code.highlighter-rouge 0 0 1rem
        |  for something more consistent with other elements.
    .bd-example
        blockquote.blockquote
            p
                | Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Integer posuere erat a ante.
            footer
                | Someone famous in 
                cite(title='Source Title') Source Title
    h3#inline-elements Inline elements
    p
        | The 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;abbr&gt;
        |  element receives basic styling to make it stand out amongst paragraph text.
    .bd-example
        | Nulla 
        abbr(title='attribute') attr
        |  vitae elit libero, a pharetra augue.
    h3#summary Summary
    p
        | The default 
        code.highlighter-rouge cursor
        |  on summary is 
        code.highlighter-rouge text
        | , so we reset that to 
        code.highlighter-rouge pointer
        |  to convey that the element can be interacted with by clicking on it.
    .bd-example
        details
            summary Some details
            p More info about the details.
        details(open='')
            summary Even more details
            p Here are even more details about the details.
    h2#html5-hidden-attribute
        | HTML5 
        code.highlighter-rouge [hidden]
        |  attribute
    p
        | HTML5 adds 
        a(href='https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/hidden')
            | a new global attribute named 
            code.highlighter-rouge [hidden]
        | , which is styled as 
        code.highlighter-rouge display: none
        |  by default. Borrowing an idea from 
        a(href='https://purecss.io/') PureCSS
        | , we improve upon this default by making 
        code.highlighter-rouge [hidden] { display: none !important; }
        |  to help prevent its 
        code.highlighter-rouge display
        |  from getting accidentally overridden. While 
        code.highlighter-rouge [hidden]
        |  isn’t natively supported by IE10, the explicit declaration in our CSS gets around that problem.
    figure.highlight
        pre.
    .bd-callout.bd-callout-warning
        h5#jquery-incompatibility jQuery incompatibility
        p
            code.highlighter-rouge [hidden]
            |  is not compatible with jQuery’s 
            code.highlighter-rouge $(...).hide()
            |  and 
            code.highlighter-rouge $(...).show()
            |  methods. Therefore, we don’t currently especially endorse 
            code.highlighter-rouge [hidden]
            |  over other techniques for managing the 
            code.highlighter-rouge display
            |  of elements.
    p
        | To merely toggle the visibility of an element, meaning its 
        code.highlighter-rouge display
        |  is not modified and the element can still affect the flow of the document, use 
        a(href='/docs/utilities/visibility/')
            | the 
            code.highlighter-rouge .invisible
            |  class
        |  instead.
